04/11/2008
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat decided on Monday (November 3rd) to speed up reunification talks by meeting twice next week. 
At their sixth face-to-face meeting, they discussed power sharing and legislation in the future federal state. 
They will meet again on November 11th and November 14th, UN Special Representative Taye-Brook Zerihoun told reporters after the meeting. 
He said Talat and Christofias are "moving forward" but refused to answer questions about whether they are closer to a power-sharing agreement. 
(CNA, Famagusta Gazette, Reuters, Philelefteros, Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency - 03/11/08)
